==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aiglet
<hw>Aig"let</hw>
<pr>(⟦amac⟧g"l⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>aiguillette</ets> point, tagged point, dim. of <ets>aiguilee</ets>
needle, fr. LL. <ets>acucula</ets> for <ets>acicula</ets>, dim. of L.
<ets>acus</ets> needle, pin; cf. OF. <ets>agleter</ets> to hook on. See
<er>Acute</er>, and cf. <er>Aiguillette</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
tag of a lace or of the points, braids, or cords formerly used in dress.
They were sometimes formed into small images. <as>Hence,
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>aglet</xex> baby⟦rdquo⟧ (<au>Shak.</au>), an <ex>aglet</ex>
image.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Haberdashery)</fld> <def>A round white
staylace.</def> <rj><au>Beck.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agley</ent>⟦br⟧

